It is likely that the category you fall into is full. If you tell me what your year and major is, we can look it up for you. Keep in mind that many seats in this course are reserved for incoming freshmen in both majors. 

If you look at Getting into EE Classes, you'll see that all those seats are definitely not reserved for only EECS majors. In fact, we reserved some seats for L&S undeclared 2nd and 3rd years this fall.

children.subject: 2nd-year CS-intended did fill a while ago, unfortunately. If you filled out the form and were not enrolled, it's because your category is full, your lab and/or discussion are full, the class is full, and/or you're at max units.
It's weird since I enrolled on the first day of Phase 1 for me (Apr 28). I don't think that 2nd year CS-intended would fill up by then.
This continues to be a very impacted class and is required by several majors.
Do you think 2nd year CS-intended still has a chance to get in off the waitlist?   Or is it unlikeley?

It's really hard to know at this point. I think by end of July we'll have a much better idea as the new students will have enrolled by then. If there is a class you need to prioritize over EE16A, you might want to do so. If you can wait it out, it could definitely work out in the end, but it's hard to know how many 1st-semester students are going to want to take EE16A in the fall.

Just finished my freshman year and I'm CS-intended. Thanks! 

Btw if it helps, I'm enrolled in another class whose lecture happens at the same time.. I submitted the conflict form that's on this Piazza for it a while ago tho
There were seats added to your category. If you're waitlisted it is because your lab and/or discussion are full, and/or you have a time conflict. See post @3689 for time conflict information.
Hello, I am a CS intended junior transfer student. It seems like I have the same issue with getting into EE16A. I'm on the waitlist (#241). Is it because I am undeclared?

If you're enrolled and you switch to a full secondary section, you will be waitlisted. At that point, we can't guarantee your enrollment anymore. If space opens up in a different lab, you could switch by using the "Options" feature. Once the class starts, you will want to check with the TAs of the course on whether switching is OK. I imagine there is a lot of movement in the first few weeks.

Hi, I'm a rising sophomore, L&S CS intended, and I'm currently enrolled in EE 16A, but I want to switch my lab. However, if I swapped my lab, would I still be able to get into the class with all the people on the waitlist? If I waited until school started, would I be able to switch labs by telling the TA (like how for 61A we can enroll in any discussion and lab but go to a different one)

history.content: For some reason there's 648/882 open seats in 16A, but I and 263 others are on the waitlist (I'm position 113)... does anyone know why? There can't be that many reserved seats for EECS majors lol
